f=Cybersecurity/veil/marketplace/privacy-by-design/SKILL.md · in=Enforce data protection across full lifecycle classification handling through encryption, retention, disposal aligned GDPR principles industry best practices. skill implements "privacy design" "privacy default" obligations under GDPR Article 25, ensuring data protection built systems processes start, added afterthought. · p=Data protection compliance checkbox; it's trust imperative. customers, partners, regulators see data protection built business operates bolted audit looms they trust organization their data. skill provides operational controls make trust real: encryption, retention limits, access controls, lifecycle management. · wu=Designing new system, feature, process handles personal sensitive data., Reviewing existing system data protection compliance., Responding data subject request (access, deletion, portability)., Preparing DPIA (Data Protection Impact Assessment)., Auditing data handling practices against GDPR equivalent regulations. · h3:Classification-Based Controls=Data protection controls applied proportional classification data: · h3:Classification-Based Controls=\| Classification \| Encryption at Rest \| Encryption in Transit \| Retention Limit \| Access Control \| · h3:Classification-Based Controls=\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\| · h3:Classification-Based Controls=\| PUBLIC \| Not required \| TLS recommended \| As needed \| Basic \| · h3:Classification-Based Controls=\| INTERNAL \| Not required \| TLS required \| As needed \| Role-based \| · h3:Classification-Based Controls=\| CONFIDENTIAL \| Required (AES-256) \| TLS 1.2+ required \| 5 years \| Strict need-to-know \| · h3:Classification-Based Controls=\| RESTRICTED \| Required (AES-256 + HSM) \| TLS 1.2+ required \| 7+ years \| Strict + formal approval \| · h3:GDPR Alignment=**Article 5 — Principles:** · h3:GDPR Alignment=Lawfulness, fairness, transparency, Purpose limitation, Data minimisation, Accuracy, Storage limitation (retention limits above), Integrity confidentiality (encryption controls above), Accountability (logging documentation below) · h3:GDPR Alignment=**Article Data Protection Design Default:** · h3:GDPR Alignment=Privacy controls built system design, added later, Default settings privacy-protective, Data minimisation default collect what's necessary, Pseudonymisation where possible · h3:GDPR Alignment=**Article Security Processing:** · h3:GDPR Alignment=Encryption of personal data, Ability ensure ongoing confidentiality, integrity, availability, resilience, Ability restore access data timely manner after incident, Regular testing effectiveness security measures · h3:Collection=collect data necessary stated purpose (data minimisation), Obtain consent required (opt-in, pre-ticked), Document lawful basis processing, Provide clear privacy notice point collection · h3:Storage=Store appropriate classification tier (encryption, access controls applied), Retention limit enforced (automatic deletion archiving), Access logged and audited · h3:Processing=Purpose limitation process purpose data collected, Access strict need-to-know basis, Processing logged · h3:Transfer=Encryption transit (TLS 1.2+ minimum), Cross-border transfer safeguards (SCCs, adequacy decisions, BCRs), Third-party processor agreements place · h3:Disposal=Secure deletion end retention period (overwrite digital, shred physical), Certification deletion required, Retain deletion records compliance requirements · of=`## Data Protection Review: [system/process/data set] \· Classification: [tier per classification policy] \· GDPR Alignment: \· Article 5 (principles): [compliant / gaps identified] \· Article 25 (by design/default): [compliant / gaps identified]` · pr=**Privacy default** privacy-protective settings default. **Data minimisation** collect what's needed; you don't need it, don't collect it. **Protection follows data** encryption, access controls, retention apply wherever data goes. **Purpose limitation** data collected one purpose reused another without consent legal basis. **Accountability** document everything; it's documented, didn't happen. · f=**No classification applied** default CONFIDENTIAL-level protection until classified; flag classification review., **Legacy system can't meet encryption requirements** compensating controls (network segmentation, strict access controls) time-boxed remediation plan; flag exception warden., **Cross-border transfer without SCCs** flag risk; recommend immediate adoption Standard Contractual Clauses. · b:with Other Skills=**veil's data-classification** (sibling): skill enforces protection controls based classification tiers defined there., **veil's DLP** (sibling): DLP enforces egress controls matching protection requirements., **veil's breach-notification** (sibling): data protection incidents trigger notification obligations., **spec/loom (Product)**: DPIA coordination new features., **dana (Engineering)**: implements encryption access controls skill prescribes., **warden**: data protection gaps compliance deficiencies register risks.